Joe Flieger Many years back I wrote a short few words I titled "The Journey" that seem to only inspire and I have been encouraged to by many to share so without further ado … We strive to be the person we love the person we want the person we can always count on but when we are so lost so confused that the person who we have been our whole life is nowhere.  The person we where yesterday is no longer the self-assuring proclaimed wonders that we remember from the day before.  All we feel is darkness where their used to be happiness and light we feel so blinded by the darkness of reality that even with all the strength in our soul we cannot seem to find a path leading us back to where we have been.  Only through the realization of what we where and what we have become do the stairs of life revel themselves ever so slightly as we pull inwards with every bone in our fiber to push on to our next state of being just one small step onwards.  With every caution and regard for only ourselves we start to rebuild the structure, that is our life.  Taking only bits and pieces of what we can barely remember of who we where and consolidating them with the realizations of darkness we once endured to form the next step on our journey.
